THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN ENACT:
1 TITLE
2 An act to provide for the incorporation of certain municipal
3 authorities to acquire, own, extend, improve, and operate sewage
4 disposal systems, water supply systems, and solid waste management
5 systems; to prescribe the rights, powers, and duties thereof; to
6 authorize contracts between such authorities and public
7 corporations; to authorize the appointment or employment of law
8 enforcement officers by certain authorities; to provide for the
9 issuance of bonds to acquire, construct, extend, or improve the
10 systems; and to prescribe penalties and provide remedies.
11 Sec. 1. As used in this act:
12 (a) "Authority", unless the context clearly implies a
13 different meaning, means an authority incorporated under section 2.
14 (b) "Constituent municipality" or "constituent municipalities"
15 includes all of the municipalities that signed or became
16 signatories of articles of incorporation of any authority
17 incorporated under this act. However, if an authority is
18 incorporated by 2 or more counties, each municipality within the
19 respective territorial limits of the counties, whether the counties
20 are original incorporators or subsequently became a constituent
21 part of the authority under section 6, is a constituent
22 municipality.
23 (c) "Indian tribe" means an Indian tribe, band, nation, or
24 other organized group or community of Indians that is recognized as
25 eligible for services by the United States secretary Secretary of
26 the interior Interior because of their status as Indians.
27 (d) "Law enforcement agency" means a law enforcement agency
28 created by a qualified authority under section 4.
THS H02305'25 (H-1) 7eoxmi

3
1 (e) (d) "Municipality" means a county, township, city, or
2 village.
3 (f) "Qualified authority" means an authority that owns or
4 operates a sewage disposal system or water supply system with a
5 weekly treatment capacity of 1,000,000,000 gallons or more.
6 (g) (e) "Sewage disposal system" includes all interceptor
7 sewers, storm sewers, sanitary sewers, combined sanitary and storm
8 sewers, sewage treatment plants, and all other plants, works,
9 instrumentalities, and properties used or useful in connection with
10 the collection, treatment, or disposal of sewage or industrial
11 wastes.
12 (h) (f) "Solid waste management system" includes all plants,
13 works, instrumentalities, and properties used or useful in
14 connection with the collection, transportation, processing, or
15 disposal of discarded or waste materials of any sort, including
16 access roads and facilities for resource recovery. Solid waste
17 management system does not include the storage or disposal of toxic
18 materials.
19 (i) (g) "Water supply system" includes all plants, works,
20 instrumentalities, and properties used or useful in connection with
21 obtaining a water supply, the treatment of water, or the
22 distribution of water.
23 Sec. 4. (1) An authority shall be is a municipal authority and
24 shall be a public body corporate with power to sue and be sued in
25 any court of this state. It shall possess An authority possesses
26 all the powers necessary to carry out the purposes of its the
27 authority's incorporation and those the powers incident thereto. to
28 the powers necessary to carry out the purpose of the authority's
29 incorporation. The enumeration of any powers of a power of an
