1 under the provisions of this act.
2 (h) Acquire, hold, and dispose of real and personal property
3 in the exercise of its the authority's powers and the performance
4 of its the authority's duties under this act.
5 (3) A qualified authority may do all of the following:
6 (a) Adopt and enforce ordinances, rules, and regulations for
7 the orderly, safe, efficient, and sanitary operation and use of any
8 of the following that are owned, operated, or maintained by the
9 qualified authority:
10 (i) Sewage disposal systems.
11 (ii) Solid waste management systems.
12 (iii) Water supply systems, projects, or facilities.
13 (b) Create a law enforcement agency within the qualified
14 authority to appoint or employ law enforcement officers.
15 (c) Adopt ordinances providing for civil fines and criminal
16 penalties for the violation of an ordinance, rule, or regulation of
17 the qualified authority adopted under this act to the same extent
18 as a city that owns a sewage disposal system, solid waste
19 management system, or water supply system under this act.
20 (d) Enforce ordinances, rules, and regulations adopted by the
21 qualified authority under this act in a court of competent
22 jurisdiction in this state.
23 Sec. 4a. (1) The Except as provided in subsection (2), an
24 authority shall may adopt rules and regulations by resolution of
25 its the authority's governing body and with concurrence by
