5 Sec. 4b. (1) Except as otherwise provided in this act, the an
6 authority may prescribe a civil fine not to exceed $1,000.00 for
7 the violation of a rule or regulation adopted and promulgated under
8 this act. If a civil fine is prescribed, it shall must be
9 prescribed in the rule or regulation.
10 (2) Except as otherwise provided in this act, a qualified
11 authority may prescribe a civil fine not to exceed $1,000.00 for
12 the violation of an ordinance, rule, or regulation adopted by the
13 governing body of the qualified authority under this act. If a
14 civil fine is prescribed, it must be prescribed in the ordinance,
15 rule, or regulation.
16 (3) A fine assessed under this section shall must be
17 distributed pursuant to section 8379 of the revised judicature act
18 of 1961, 1961 PA 236, MCL 600.8379.
19 Sec. 4c. The An authority may provide in its the authority's
20 rules and regulations, and a qualified authority may provide in the
21 qualified authority's ordinances, rules, and regulations, for
22 either or both of the following prohibitions and penalties:
23 (a) A person who knowingly submits or prepares for submission
24 to the an authority or a qualified authority a false statement,
25 representation, or certification is guilty of a misdemeanor,
26 punishable by imprisonment for not more than 90 days, or a fine of
27 not more than $500.00, or both. Each violation constitutes a
28 separate and distinct offense.
29 (b) A person who knowingly tampers with or alters a monitoring
