1 device or process, causing inaccurate readings or results, is
2 guilty of a misdemeanor, punishable by imprisonment for not more
3 than 90 days, or a fine of not more than $500.00, or both. Each
4 violation constitutes a separate and distinct offense.
5 Sec. 4d. (1) Subject to subsections (2) and (3), (9), rules
6 and regulations promulgated adopted by an authority, other than a
7 qualified authority, under this act are enforceable by the
8 authority , its that adopted the rules and regulations, the
9 authority's constituent municipalities, and municipalities or
10 Indian tribes that have contracted with the authority for the
11 furnishing of service pursuant to under section 10. A person
12 charged with enforcement of those the rules and regulations may
13 issue a citation or an appearance ticket to any person who that is
14 reasonably believed to have violated a rule or regulation
15 promulgated adopted under this act.
16 (2) The An authority, other than a qualified authority, shall
17 exercise its the authority's enforcement powers under this act
18 against a violator within a municipality.
19 (3) Ordinances, rules, and regulations adopted by a qualified
20 authority under this act are enforceable by the qualified
21 authority, the qualified authority's constituent municipalities,
22 and municipalities or Indian tribes that have contracted with the
23 qualified authority for the furnishing of water, sewage disposal,
24 or waste management services under section 10. A person authorized
25 to enforce the ordinances, rules, or regulations may issue a
26 citation or appearance ticket to any person that is reasonably
27 believed to have violated an ordinance, rule, or regulation adopted
28 by the qualified authority under this act. The ordinances, rules,
29 and regulations of a qualified authority may be enforced by a peace
