9
1 officer under section 2a of chapter IV of the code of criminal
2 procedure, 1927 PA 175, MCL 764.2a.
3 (4) A law enforcement agency established by a qualified
4 authority may grant to a law enforcement officer of that law
5 enforcement agency the same powers, immunities, and authorities
6 granted by the law of this state to a peace officer and a police
7 officer to detect crime, to enforce the criminal laws of this
8 state, and to enforce state laws, including laws under this act,
9 local ordinances, and any ordinances, rules, and regulations
10 adopted by the qualified authority. A copy of the documentation of
11 a grant of authority under this subsection must be filed with the
12 Michigan commission on law enforcement standards created under the
13 Michigan commission on law enforcement standards act, 1965 PA 203,
14 MCL 28.601 to 28.615.
15 (5) To the extent permitted or required by federal law, a law
16 enforcement officer of a qualified authority may enforce federal
17 laws and regulations applicable to the security of sewage disposal
18 systems, solid waste management systems, or water supply systems.
19 (6) A qualified authority may administer a sworn oath of
20 office to a law enforcement officer of the qualified authority
21 conferring the power on the law enforcement officer to administer
22 the general criminal laws of this state.
23 (7) A law enforcement officer of a qualified authority granted
24 the authority of a law enforcement officer under subsections (4)
25 and (5) is a peace officer of this state with the authority of a
26 police officer of this state under this act and under the code of
27 criminal procedure, 1927 PA 175, MCL 760.1 to 777.69.
28 (8) A law enforcement agency of a qualified authority shall
29 submit monthly uniform crime reports pertaining to crimes occurring
